<Layout title="Hefferon Ch.3 — Maps Between Spaces" favicon="📐">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/linear-algebra/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">← back to linear algebra</a>

    <h1>Maps Between Spaces</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 text-sm mb-6">Jim Hefferon · GFDL + CC BY-SA 2.5 · <a href="https://hefferon.net/linearalgebra/">Linear Algebra</a></p>

    <div class="bg-zinc-800 rounded-lg p-5 mb-8 callout">
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width:none">A <strong>linear map</strong> (homomorphism) preserves addition and scalar multiplication. Every linear map from R^n to R^m is multiplication by an m-by-n matrix. The <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rank%E2%80%93nullity_theorem"><img src="/reading/wikipedia.svg" alt="wp" style="display:inline;height:1em;vertical-align:-0.1em;margin-right:0.2em;"/>rank-nullity theorem</a> says: dimension of domain = dimension of image + dimension of kernel. Always.</p>
    </div>

    <!-- 1. Linear maps -->
    <h3>Linear maps</h3>
    <p>A function h: V to W is <strong>linear</strong> if h(v + w) = h(v) + h(w) and h(c*v) = c*h(v) for all vectors v, w and scalars c. Linearity means the map respects the vector space structure. It never bends straight lines or shifts the origin.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Domain/codomain ovals with arrows -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 380 180" class="w-full max-w-md" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Domain oval -->
        <ellipse cx="100" cy="90" rx="70" ry="60" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="100" y="165" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5">V (domain)</text>
        <!-- Codomain oval -->
        <ellipse cx="280" cy="90" rx="70" ry="60" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.4"/>
        <text x="280" y="165" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.5">W (codomain)</text>
        <!-- Points in domain -->
        <circle cx="80" cy="65" r="3" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="68" y="60" fill="#60a5fa" font-size="10">v1</text>
        <circle cx="90" cy="100" r="3" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="76" y="110" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="10">v2</text>
        <circle cx="115" cy="75" r="3" fill="#34d399" fill-opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="120" y="70" fill="#34d399" font-size="10">v3</text>
