    <!-- Translation notes -->
    <h3>Translation notes</h3>
    <p>Hefferon builds up to the rank-nullity theorem through homomorphisms, isomorphisms, and the first isomorphism theorem (V/ker h is isomorphic to im h). This page focuses on the computational core. The chapter also covers composition of maps (matrix multiplication) and invertibility.</p>

